Usage of run:
  -abort-error-sustain duration
    	sustain window for the error-rate abort threshold (default 10s)
  -abort-on-error-pct float
    	abort the run if error rate stays over this fraction (0..1) for --abort-error-sustain; 0 disables
  -abort-on-p99-ms int
    	abort the run if the p99 of the abort window's latency stays over this for --abort-p99-sustain; 0 disables
  -abort-p99-sustain duration
    	sustain window for the p99 abort threshold (default 30s)
  -abort-window-max-samples int
    	S3: cap on the abort/progress latency ring buffer; 0 disables the cap (legacy). Bounds the per-tick percentile sort under sustained high publish rates. WARNING: when peak_rps × max(abort-*-sustain) > cap, retention is compressed below the sustain interval and the abort watcher cannot fire; it emits a slog.Warn 'abort watcher deafened by sample cap' so the silent no-fire is detectable. Size cap >= peak_rps × max_sustain to keep the watcher functional. (default 10000)
  -allow-concurrent
    	allow multiple concurrent loadgen runs against the same SUT (default refuses to start when another active run is detected)
  -auto-warmup
    	run a brief messaging-pipeline phase to populate message IDs before read scenarios that need them (default true)
  -auto-warmup-rate int
    	publish rate (rps) during the auto-warmup phase (default 200)
  -connections int
    	number of NATS data connections (per-user fan-out); 1 reuses the observer connection (default 1)
  -csv string
    	optional csv output path
  -duration duration
    	run duration (default 1m0s)
  -inject string
    	injection point: frontdoor|canonical (default "frontdoor")
  -js-async-max-pending int
    	S5: max in-flight async JetStream publishes for canonical inject; 0 falls back to sync js.PublishMsg (legacy / bisection) (default 4096)
  -liveness-failures int
    	consecutive liveness probe failures required to abort the run (default 3)
  -liveness-interval duration
    	mid-run SUT liveness probe interval; 0 disables. Default 10s × 3 failures = 30s detection so the watcher can fire on the default 60s --duration. (default 10s)
  -liveness-timeout duration
    	per-probe timeout. Aligned with --request-timeout default so a slow-but-up SUT trips the saturation watcher (exit 2) before the liveness watcher (exit 3). (default 5s)
  -nats-creds-dir string
    	directory of *.creds files; data conns rotate through them (C2 prep — auth-service must be in compose stack for SUT-side validation)
  -preset string
    	preset name
  -progress-interval duration
    	live progress log interval; 0 disables (default 10s)
  -ramp-duration duration
    	time to climb from --ramp-from to --ramp-to
  -ramp-from int
    	starting rate (rps) for a ramped run; 0 disables ramping
  -ramp-shape string
    	ramp curve: linear|exponential (default "linear")
  -ramp-to int
    	ending rate (rps) for a ramped run; 0 disables ramping
  -rate int
    	target msgs/sec (default 500)
  -raw-poll-interval duration
    	raw-consistency scenario: interval between visibility polls per path (default 10ms)
  -raw-timeout duration
    	raw-consistency scenario: per-message poll timeout before declaring not-visible (default 5s)
  -readiness-timeout duration
    	deadline for the readiness probe to succeed (default 30s)
  -request-timeout duration
    	per-request timeout for read scenarios (default 5s)
  -run-ttl duration
    	max age for an active runlock entry before it is considered orphaned and ignored (default 2h0m0s)
  -scenario string
    	scenario: messaging-pipeline|history-read|search-read|room-rpc|raw-consistency|room-open (default "messaging-pipeline")
  -seed int
    	RNG seed (default 42)
  -settle-interval duration
    	settle phase: poll interval between probe rounds (default 500ms)
  -settle-probes int
    	settle phase: number of recent message IDs to probe (0 disables) (default 20)
  -settle-timeout duration
    	settle phase: max time to wait for probes to succeed before declaring failure (default 30s)
  -skip-readiness
    	skip the pre-run readiness probe for read scenarios
  -warmup duration
    	warmup window (samples discarded) (default 10s)
